-- Hellenic Petroleum Said to Issue Tender to Sell May Diesel
-- B y   R u p e r t   R o w l i n g
-- 2012-05-02T16:43:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-02/hellenic-petroleum-said-to-issue-tender-to-sell-diesel-in-may.html
Hellenic Petroleum SA (ELPE) , Greece’s
largest refiner, issued a tender to sell one cargo of diesel in
May, according to two people who received the document.  The tender is for 30,000 metric tons of ultra-low-sulfur
diesel for loading either from the Greek port of Elefsis or the
Aspropyrgos refinery, the people said today. No traders or media
relations officials were available, said a person who answered
the phone today at Hellenic’s office in  Athens .  The tender details are as follows:  To contact the reporter on this story:
